               <interp inst="t17570914-9" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17570914-9" type="year" value="1757"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17570914-9" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17570914"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17570914-9" type="date" value="17570914"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17570914-9-off52-c87" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-defend102 t17570914-9-off52 t17570914-9-verdict56"></join>
         
               <p>306. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17570914-9-defend102" type="defendantName">
                     Bartholomew 
                     Godfield 
                  <interp inst="t17570914-9-defend102" type="surname" value="Godfield"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-defend102" type="given" value="Bartholomew"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-defend102" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17570914-9-off52" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-off52" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-off52" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               stealing one silver watch, value 3 l one cloth coat, value 20 s. one stuff damask waistcoat, value 10 s. the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17570914-9-victim104" type="victimName">
                           Nathaniel 
                           Stainton 
                        <interp inst="t17570914-9-victim104" type="surname" value="Stainton"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17570914-9-victim104" type="given" value="Nathaniel"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17570914-9-victim104" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-off52 t17570914-9-victim104"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , in the dwelling house of 
                     <persName id="t17570914-9-person105">
                        Edward 
                        Scandret 
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person105" type="surname" value="Scandret"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17570914-9-person105" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17570914-9-person105" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  
               
                  </rs>, <rs id="t17570914-9-cd53" type="crimeDate">August 6</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-off52 t17570914-9-cd53"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17570914-9-person106">
                  Nathaniel 
                  Stainton 
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-person106" type="surname" value="Stainton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person106" type="given" value="Nathaniel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I lodge in <placeName id="t17570914-9-crimeloc54">Clement's lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17570914-9-crimeloc54" type="placeName" value="Clement's lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17570914-9-crimeloc54" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-off52 t17570914-9-crimeloc54"></join>, at the house of 
               <persName id="t17570914-9-person107">
                  Edward 
                  Scandret 
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-person107" type="surname" value="Scandret"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person107" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person107" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; the prisoner lodg'd and lay with me in the same bed, and had about seven nights. I am a 
               <persName id="t17570914-9-victim108" type="victimName">
                  carpenter
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-victim108" type="given" value="carpenter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-victim108" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-off52 t17570914-9-victim108"></join>
                  </persName>
            . He told us he <rs id="t17570914-9-deflabel55" type="occupation">taught the French language</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-defend102 t17570914-9-deflabel55"></join>. I never saw him before he came to lodge with me. On the 6th of August, in the morning betwixt four and five I awak'd, and miss'd my watch out of my fob, and a coat and waistcoat out of my chest. My landlord ran out at the gate, and found a shirt of mine on the ground; then my landlord went to the man where he lodg'd before, and told him the case, and he took him with the watch in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17570914-9-person109">
                  Thomas 
                  Wills 
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-person109" type="surname" value="Wills"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person109" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person109" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner had lodg'd with me before he went to lodge with the prosecutor. I met with him in the street, and took him with the prosecutor's watch in his pocket, which he deliver'd to me, (produced in court, and deposed to by the prosecutor.) He own'd before justice Fielding where he had sold the coat and waistcoat in the Minories, where I found them, ( produced in court and deposed by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17570914-9-person110">
                  David 
                  Coleman 
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-person110" type="surname" value="Coleman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person110" type="given" value="David"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the Minories, and bought this coat and waistcoat of a man like the prisoner, I think it is he, but can't swear to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17570914-9-person111">
                  Joyce 
                  Scandret 
               <interp inst="t17570914-9-person111" type="surname" value="Scandret"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person111" type="given" value="Joyce"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-person111" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The robbery was committed in my house. The prisoner and prosecutor lay together. I let in the prisoner at about eleven o'clock,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175709140007"></xptr> and heard no more of them till before five, when the prosecutor told us he had been rob'd; he then was very ill of a fever, but the prisoner was gone out. I heard him go out. He was taken about three hours after, and I was at the fetching the cloaths from the Minories.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I am no guilty, no body can swear they saw me take a de tings.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17570914-9-verdict56" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-verdict56" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>, <rs id="t17570914-9-punish57" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17570914-9-punish57" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17570914-9-defend102 t17570914-9-punish57"></join>
               Death
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
